  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a survey of factors which affect a pathologically defined early or delayed diagnosis
      of IgA nephropathy in Guangdong General Hospital, Guangzhou, China. An early or delayed
      diagnosis of IgA nephropathy is pathologically defined using the recently published Oxford
      classification of IgA nephropathy. The factors to be surveyed include health examination
      including urine test, socioeconomic status of patients including education,etc.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
